.TH FLOWCOIN-MINER "1" "April 2026" "FlowCoin Core 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
flowcoin\-miner \- standalone CPU RandomX miner for FlowCoin
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B flowcoin\-miner
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Standalone CPU\-only RandomX miner that talks to a running
\fBflowcoind\fR(1) instance over JSON\-RPC. Requests block templates via
\fBgetblocktemplate\fR, searches for a qualifying nonce in a thread pool,
and submits solved blocks via \fBsubmitblock\fR.
.PP
Output style follows XMRig conventions: a banner at startup, then
timestamped tagged events, a \fBspeed\fR line every ten seconds, and
\fBaccepted\fR / \fBrejected\fR events per submit.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-o\fR \fIURL\fR, \fB\-\-url\fR \fIURL\fR
Node RPC endpoint (default: \fIhttp://127.0.0.1:9334\fR).
.TP
\fB\-\-cookie\fR \fIPATH\fR
Read HTTP Basic auth from a Bitcoin\-Core\-style cookie file.
Typical value: \fI~/.flowcoin/.cookie\fR.
.TP
\fB\-u\fR \fIUSER\fR, \fB\-\-user\fR \fIUSER\fR
Explicit RPC username (alternative to \fB\-\-cookie\fR).
.TP
\fB\-p\fR \fIPASS\fR, \fB\-\-pass\fR \fIPASS\fR
Explicit RPC password (alternative to \fB\-\-cookie\fR).
.TP
\fB\-t\fR \fIN\fR, \fB\-\-threads\fR \fIN\fR
Number of worker threads (default: one per logical CPU).
.TP
\fB\-a\fR \fIADDR\fR, \fB\-\-address\fR \fIADDR\fR
Coinbase reward address in Bech32 v0 format (\fIfl1q...\fR). If omitted,
the node's wallet supplies a fresh address per block.
.TP
\fB\-\-key\fR \fIPATH\fR
Ed25519 miner signing key file (default: \fI~/.flowcoin/miner_key\fR,
generated on first run).
.TP
\fB\-b\fR \fISEC\fR, \fB\-\-benchmark\fR \fISEC\fR
Run RandomX for \fISEC\fR seconds, print H/s, exit. No node required.
.TP
\fB\-\-light\fR
Use the 256 MiB cache instead of the 2 GiB dataset. Slower per thread
but usable on memory\-constrained machines or for quick benchmarks.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-color\fR
Disable ANSI colour escapes in the terminal output.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# Default — full mode, all threads, cookie auth, localhost node
flowcoin\-miner \-\-cookie ~/.flowcoin/.cookie

# Mine against a remote node with explicit credentials
flowcoin\-miner \-o http://node.example.lan:9334 \-u flow \-p secret

# 10\-second RandomX benchmark
flowcoin\-miner \-\-benchmark 10

# 10\-second benchmark in light mode (no 2 GiB allocation)
flowcoin\-miner \-\-benchmark 10 \-\-light

# Four threads, fixed coinbase address
flowcoin\-miner \-\-cookie ~/.flowcoin/.cookie \\
                \-\-threads 4 \-\-address fl1q...
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.flowcoin/.cookie\fR
RPC authentication cookie generated by flowcoind at startup.
.TP
\fI~/.flowcoin/miner_key\fR
Ed25519 signing key used to sign submitted blocks.
.SH NOTES
Mining is CPU\-only by design. There is no OpenCL, no CUDA, no GPU
path. A GPU port would be at best 10x slower per watt (RandomX is
DRAM\-bandwidth\-bound, not gate\-count\-bound) and is not planned.
.PP
The 2 GiB RandomX dataset takes ~1.5 s to allocate on a fast CPU.
If it stays at 0 H/s for more than ~10 s, fall back to
\fB\-\-light\fR.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR flowcoind (1),
.BR flowcoin\-cli (1),
.BR flowcoin\-tx (1)
